<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-01-10T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-01-10T20:00:00-05:00" n="431" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">561.35E1/110: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-01-10T20:00:00-05:00">January
                                    10, 1936—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>8. Your No. 4, January 3. Please inform the Foreign Office in response to
                            their informal note that this Government is sympathetic to and
                            interested in the general possibility of a new international sugar
                            agreement. The uncertainty recently created regarding governmental
                            policy in the agricultural field<note n="7" xml:id="d431fn7">By the
                                invalidation of the Agricultural Adjustment Act (approved May 12,
                                1933; 48 Stat. 31) on January 6, 1936, by the Supreme Court; 297 U.
                                S. 1.</note> makes it necessary, however, to postpone reply to the
                            British communication. As soon as this uncertainty is ended, we will
                            formulate our views.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>